\par    \tab }{\b\fs24 Trade enclaves}{\fs24  are situated in the towns and cities of other races and subraces for the purpose of conducting trade. They may be fortified houses or stone forts for the traders, their guards, and their families.
\par    \tab }{\b\fs24 Ghettoes }{\fs24 are areas within cities and towns of othe
r races where clusters of dwarves live. This could be a wealthy city block inhabited by well-to-do dwarf merchants and craftsmen or an impoverished shanty town where dwarves eke out a living as best they can.
\par    \tab }{\b\fs24 A family stronghold}{\fs24 
 is home to a single family of dwarves. They are small and often consist of a single house or underground cavern inhabited by a family. Dwarves who live in family strongholds tend to be very reclusive and clannish.
